<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - DISASSEMBLY - COUNTERSHAFT
        DISASSEMBLY AND REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT DISASSEMBLY AND REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The countershaft gears are easily pressed off and on this shaft. The rolled involute splines
                provide increased torque capacity. Two counter shafts are illustrated,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300660">Figure 60</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300660" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300660" filename="../figg13/g1300660.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Countershaft Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When assembling this countershaft, make sure the gears are positioned correctly, see
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300661">Figure 61</hotlnk>:
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300661" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300661" filename="../figg13/g1300661.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Assembling Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">3rd speed gear recessed ID faces 2nd gear. (2nd gear is part of countershaft.)</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Spacer (3rd &#38; 4th gear).</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">4th speed gear, 6th speed gear or overdrive (13MAH); 5th speed gear or direct drive
                    (13MAG).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Countershaft drive gear hub faces 6th speed gear or 5th speed gear on direct drive shift
                    unit.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
